{{ja-noun|かばね}}

# a [[clan]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|氏|tr=uji}}
# {{lb|ja|historical}} a kind of [[hereditary]] [[title]] bestowed to clans in ancient Japan

* {{ja-r|姓%書|かばね%-がき}}: {{qualifier|historical}} someone's [[full name]], written out with the status of their [[clan]] [[append]]ed
* {{ja-r|姓%名|かばね% な|[[clan]] [[name]]}}
* {{ja-r|八色の姓|^やくさ の ^かばね}}, {{ja-r|八色の姓|^はっしき の ^かばね}}: a specific set of eight ''kabane'' [[title]]s [[promulgate]]d by {{w|Emperor Tenmu}} in 675 {{CE}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=o|しょう}}

{{IPAchar|/siau/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɕjɔː/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɕoː/}}

From {{bor|ja|ltc|sort=しょう|-}} {{ltc-l|姓}}.  The ''[[呉音#Japanese|goon]]'', so likely the initial borrowing.  Compare modern {{cog|hak|-}} reading ''siang''.

This reading is less common than ''sei'' above.

{{ja-noun|しょう|hhira=しやう}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=しょう|uncommon}} [[surname]], [[family name]]
# {{lb|ja|sort=しょう|uncommon}} [[clan]]

* {{ja-r|上姓|じょうしょう}}
* {{ja-r|下姓|げしょう}}
* {{ja-r|小姓|こしょう}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=irr|しょう|k1=そう}}

A shift from ''shō'' above to use the {{m|ja|直音||tr=chokuon|"[[straight]]" [[pronunciation]]|pos=dropping out any {{IPAchar|/j/}} or {{IPAchar|/w/}} glides}}.<ref name="KDJ"/>

This reading is not used in modern Japanese, and is only found in historical texts, such as the ''{{w|Utsubo Monogatari}}'' from the late 900s.
